###########################
#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
"PGML.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

###########################
#  Setup

Context()->variables->add(t=>"Real");
Context()->flags->set(
  tolerance => 0.051,
  tolType => "absolute",
);

$c = random(20, 30);
$a = random(4, 8);
$b = sqrt($c**2 - $a**2);

#for solution
$asq = $a**2;
$csq = $c**2;
$diff = $csq - $asq;

###########################
#  Main text

BEGIN_PGML
Gerry plans to place [`[$c]`]-foot ladder against the side of his house to clean his gutters. The bottom of the ladder will be [`[$a]`] feet from the house.  How far up the side of the house will the ladder reach? Round to the nearest tenth.

[_______________]{$b}feet


END_PGML


############################
#  Solution

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
When the ladder leans against the wall, it creates a right triangle.  We can use the pythagorean formula to set up an equation.

[`a^2 + b^2 = c^2`]

[`a = [$a]`]

[`b = x`]

[`c = [$c]`]

[`[$a]^2 + x^2 = [$c]^2`]

[`[$asq] + x^2 = [$csq]`]

[`x^2 = [$diff]`]

[`x = \sqrt{[$diff]} = [$b]`]
END_PGML_SOLUTION

COMMENT('MathObject version. Uses PGML.');

ENDDOCUMENT();